  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In France, the Afssaps is the body in charge of the evaluation of pharmacodependance. In
      order to fulfil its mission, the Afssaps has created a network of 11 Centres for Evaluation
      and Information on Pharmacodependance (CEIP), coordinated by the Drugs and Psychotropics
      Unit. Pharmacodependence notifications issued by professionals are collected by each Centre
      which evaluates them. Nantes' CEIP created an original tool to harmonize case reporting and
      make it possible to homogeneously evaluate the seriousness of pharmacodependence cases as
      each CEIP had his own way of analysing his cases. The aim of this study is to assess this
      tool.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
